                                                            <h1>D R U M E R S</h1>
                                                            <br>
                                                            <h3>Mike Portnoy:</h3>
                                                            <br>
                                                            <br>
                                                            <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/44/Transatlantic_au_Night_of_the_Prog_-_12_%2814524207019%29_%28cropped%29.jpg/800px-Transatlantic_au_Night_of_the_Prog_-_12_%2814524207019%29_%28cropped%29.jpg"
                                                            width="350" height="400"> <br>
                                                            <strong style="color: rgb(59, 11, 104);">Mike Portnoy </strong> (born in april 20,1967) is the most first 
                                                            guy to talk about in every topic of metal drummers. Obviously,
                                                            Mike Portnoy is the drummer of the most prog metal band <mark>Dream Theater.</mark>
                                                            He left the band for some years but now he's back again.
                                                            The amazing thing of him is he puts complicated double kick patterns in the songs 
                                                            which makes the drumming really amusing to listen. Also they're are some many reasons
                                                            why he's so entertaining. He also played as guest member in many famous bands like
                                                            <mark>Avenged Sevenfold, Joe Satriani,Twisted Sister,Metal Allegiance,
                                                                BPMD and Yellow Matter Custurd.</mark> Besides Dream Theater, He also has a band called <div style="color: rgb(28, 58, 89);">"The Winery Dogs"</div>
                                                                which is also in the level of Dream Theater. <br>
                                                                <br>
                                                                <h3>Joey Jordison:</h3>
                                                                
                                                                <img src="https://variety.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Joey-Jordison.jpg?w=1000&h=563&crop=1"
                                                                width="400" height="250"> <br>
                                                                <strong> Jonas "Joey" Jordison</strong> (April 26, 1975 – July 26, 2021) was an American musician. 
                                                                He was the original drummer of the nu metal band Slipknot,
                                                                 in which he was designated #1. He played in bands like
                                                                 <div id="n">Murderdolls, Rob Zombies, Metallica and KoRn.</div> <br> <br>
                                                                 <h3>Danny Carey:</h3>
                                                                 <img src="https://maubrecht.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/danny-carey-opener.jpg" alt="Danny Carey" height="400">
                                                                 <br>
                                                                 <br>
                                                                <strong> Daniel Edwin "Danny" Carey,</strong> born May 10, 1961 in Lawrence, Kansas,
                                                                  is an American drummer and instrumentalist best known for his work in American Grammy Award-winning progressive rock band Tool.
                                                                   He has also contributed to albums by and played with such artists as <div style="color: rgb(31, 31, 60);"> Green Jellÿ, Pigface, Skinny Puppy, Adrian Belew of King Crimson,
                                                                    Carole King, Collide, The Wild Blue Yonder, Lusk, and the Melvins.</div> <br>
